# SaaS Starter Kit — API Test File
# Works with VS Code REST Client extension and JetBrains HTTP Client
#
# QUICK START
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Start services: pnpm docker:up
# 2. Run migrations: pnpm db:migrate
# 3. Start API + Admin: cd apps/api && pnpm dev   (then: cd apps/admin && pnpm dev)
# 4. Get a dev token (step 2 below) and copy it into @accessToken
# 5. Select a workspace (step 3) and copy the result into @wsToken
#
# FLOW
#   dev-token → (pick tenant from GET /tenants) → POST /auth/workspace → use wsToken
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl    = http://localhost:3001
@adminUrl   = http://localhost:3002

# Paste tokens here after running the auth steps below
@accessToken = REPLACE_WITH_ACCESS_TOKEN
@wsToken     = REPLACE_WITH_WORKSPACE_TOKEN

# IDs to fill in after creation
@tenantId      = REPLACE_WITH_TENANT_ID
@membershipId  = REPLACE_WITH_MEMBERSHIP_ID
@invitationId  = REPLACE_WITH_INVITATION_ID
@inviteToken   = REPLACE_WITH_INVITE_TOKEN
@apiKeyId      = REPLACE_WITH_API_KEY_ID
@webhookId     = REPLACE_WITH_WEBHOOK_ID
@platformAdmin = REPLACE_WITH_PLATFORM_ADMIN_TOKEN


###############################################################################
# 1. HEALTH
###############################################################################

### API health check (port 3001)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### Admin health check (port 3002)
GET {{adminUrl}}/health


###############################################################################
# 2. AUTH — DEV SHORTCUTS (development only, not available in production)
###############################################################################

### [DEV] Issue tokens for any email without OAuth
# Use this to bootstrap. Copy the returned accessToken into @accessToken above.
# @name devToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/dev-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "name": "Dev User"
}

---

### [DEV] Issue a platform-admin token
# Use isPlatformAdmin:true in the user record by first creating one via admin panel,
# or seed it directly. For now, use a known platform admin email.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/dev-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "name": "Platform Admin"
}


###############################################################################
# 3. AUTH — SELECT WORKSPACE
# After getting an accessToken, list workspaces then pick one.
###############################################################################

### List workspaces for the current user (uses bare access token, no tenant yet)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

---

### Select (activate) a workspace — copy the returned accessToken into @wsToken
# @name selectWorkspace
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/workspace
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenantId": "{{tenantId}}"
}


###############################################################################
# 4. AUTH — TOKEN LIFECYCLE
###############################################################################

### Refresh access token (sends refresh_token cookie automatically in HTTP Client)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh

---

### Exchange one-time auth code for tokens (called by web app after OAuth redirect)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/exchange
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "REPLACE_WITH_ONE_TIME_CODE"
}

---

### Logout — invalidates current session
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 5. AUTH — IMPERSONATION (workspace owners only)
###############################################################################

### Start impersonating a workspace member
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/impersonate
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "targetUserId": "REPLACE_WITH_TARGET_USER_ID",
  "tenantId": "{{tenantId}}"
}

---

### Stop impersonation and return to original session
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/stop-impersonation
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 6. TENANTS / WORKSPACES
###############################################################################

### List all workspaces the current user belongs to
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

---

### Get current workspace context (tenant, subscription, flags, membership)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Update workspace name or settings (owner/admin only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "My Updated Workspace"
}

---

### Soft-delete workspace (owner only) — DANGEROUS
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 7. TEAM — MEMBERS
###############################################################################

### List workspace members
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### List workspace members — paginated
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members?limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Invite a member to the workspace (owner/admin only)
# @name inviteMember
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members/invite
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newmember@example.com",
  "role": "member"
}

---

### Invite an admin to the workspace
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members/invite
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newadmin@example.com",
  "role": "admin"
}

---

### Change a member's role (owner only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members/{{membershipId}}/role
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "admin"
}

---

### Remove a member from the workspace (owner only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/members/{{membershipId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 8. TEAM — INVITATIONS
###############################################################################

### List pending invitations (owner/admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/invitations
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Cancel a pending invitation (owner/admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/tenants/me/invitations/{{invitationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Get invitation details by token (public — no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/invitations/{{inviteToken}}

---

### Accept a workspace invitation (must be authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/invitations/{{inviteToken}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


###############################################################################
# 9. BILLING
###############################################################################

### List all public plans (no auth required — for pricing page)
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/plans

---

### Get current workspace subscription
GET {{baseUrl}}/billing/subscription
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Create a Stripe Checkout session for a plan upgrade (owner/admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/billing/checkout
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "planSlug": "growth",
  "billingCycle": "monthly"
}

---

### Create a Stripe Billing Portal session (owner/admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/billing/portal
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 10. API KEYS
###############################################################################

### List API keys for the current workspace
GET {{baseUrl}}/api-keys
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Create a new API key (owner/admin only)
# fullKey is returned ONCE — save it immediately
# @name createApiKey
POST {{baseUrl}}/api-keys
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "My Integration Key",
  "scopes": ["read:data", "write:data"]
}

---

### Create an API key with expiry
POST {{baseUrl}}/api-keys
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Short-lived Key",
  "scopes": ["read:data"],
  "expiresAt": "2027-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}

---

### Revoke an API key (owner/admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api-keys/{{apiKeyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 11. AUDIT LOGS
###############################################################################

### List audit logs (owner/admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### List audit logs — with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit-logs?limit=25&offset=0&action=api_keys.create
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Filter by resource type
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit-logs?resourceType=ApiKey&limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Filter by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit-logs?from=2026-01-01T00:00:00Z&to=2026-12-31T23:59:59Z&limit=100
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Filter by user
GET {{baseUrl}}/audit-logs?userId=REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 12. FEATURE FLAGS
###############################################################################

### List tenant-level flag overrides (owner/admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Resolve flags for the current workspace (any member)
GET {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/resolve?keys=new_dashboard,billing_v2,advanced_analytics
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Set a tenant-level flag override (owner/admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/new_dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "enabled": true,
  "config": {
    "variant": "v2"
  }
}

---

### Disable a feature flag for this tenant
PUT {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/beta_feature
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "enabled": false
}

---

### Remove a tenant-level flag override (reverts to platform default)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/feature-flags/new_dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 13. WEBHOOKS
###############################################################################

### List webhook endpoints
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### Create a webhook endpoint (owner/admin only)
# Secret is returned ONCE — save it for HMAC verification
# @name createWebhook
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://example.com/webhooks/saas",
  "events": ["member.invited", "member.removed", "subscription.upgraded"]
}

---

### Create a webhook subscribed to ALL events (empty events array)
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://example.com/webhooks/all",
  "events": []
}

---

### Update a webhook endpoint (owner/admin only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isActive": false
}

---

### Update webhook URL and events
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://example.com/webhooks/v2",
  "events": ["member.invited"],
  "isActive": true
}

---

### Delete a webhook endpoint (owner/admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### List delivery attempts for a webhook endpoint (last 25)
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}/deliveries
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}

---

### List delivery attempts — custom limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{webhookId}}/deliveries?limit=50
Authorization: Bearer {{wsToken}}


###############################################################################
# 14. ADMIN — CONTROL PLANE (platform admins only)
# Use @platformAdmin token for all requests in this section
###############################################################################

### Platform stats — tenant count, user count, revenue
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### List all tenants (paginated)
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### List tenants — filtered and paginated
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants?limit=20&offset=0&status=active&search=acme
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### Create a new tenant
# @name adminCreateTenant
POST {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Corp",
  "slug": "acme-corp"
}

---

### Create tenant with owner email and plan
POST {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Enterprise Co",
  "slug": "enterprise-co",
  "ownerEmail": "owner@enterprise.com",
  "planId": "REPLACE_WITH_PLAN_ID"
}

---

### Get a specific tenant's detail
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### Update tenant name
PATCH {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Corp (Renamed)"
}

---

### Suspend a tenant
PATCH {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "suspended"
}

---

### Reactivate a tenant
PATCH {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

---

### Soft-delete a tenant — DANGEROUS
DELETE {{adminUrl}}/admin/tenants/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### List all users (paginated)
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### List users — search and paginate
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/users?limit=20&offset=0&search=example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### List platform-level feature flag defaults
GET {{adminUrl}}/admin/feature-flags
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}

---

### Set a platform-level feature flag default
PUT {{adminUrl}}/admin/feature-flags/new_dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "enabled": true,
  "config": {
    "rollout": 100
  }
}

---

### Disable a platform feature flag for everyone by default
PUT {{adminUrl}}/admin/feature-flags/beta_feature
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "enabled": false
}

---

### Delete a platform-level feature flag default
DELETE {{adminUrl}}/admin/feature-flags/new_dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{platformAdmin}}
